"title": "7449: slavery, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7449: slavery, spiritual",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Because of sin humanity is in a state of slavery. On account of the atoning work of Jesus Christ, believers can break free from slavery to sin and enter into the glorious liberty of the children of God.</p>\n<h2>Humanity is enslaved</h2>\n<h3>To sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:33-John8:36\">JHN 8:33–8:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12-Rom6:18\">ROM 6:12–6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:7-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:7–7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3\">TIT 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:19\">2PE 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>To the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:1-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:1–4:7</a></p>\n<h3>To fear</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15\">ROM 8:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14-Heb2:15\">HEB 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the example of the true slave</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1-John13:17\">JHN 13:1–13:17</a></strong> <em>Washing feet was the responsibility of the slaves of the household.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:25–20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:42–10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:5–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Believers as slaves of God</h2>\n<h3>They are God's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:22\">ROM 6:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24\">MAT 6:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:13\">LUK 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:23-Col3:24\">COL 3:23–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:16\">1PE 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:1\">2PE 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>They are sons and heirs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:1-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:1–4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:12-Rom8:17\">ROM 8:12–8:17</a></p>\n<h3>They have friendship with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:15\">JHN 15:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:21-Jas2:23\">JAS 2:21–2:23</a></p>\n<h3>They have true freedom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:31-John8:36\">JHN 8:31–8:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:21-Gal4:31\">GAL 4:21–4:31</a></p>\n<h2>Believers as slaves of righteousness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:15-Rom6:23\">ROM 6:15–6:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Believers as slaves of others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:25–20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:42–10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19\">1CO 9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a></p>\n<h2>The image of slavery in the teaching of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:45-Matt24:51\">MAT 24:45–24:51</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:42-Luke12:46\">LUK 12:42–12:46</a> <em>Slavery involves readiness for the Master's return</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:20\">MAT 25:14–25:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12-Luke19:17\">LUK 19:12–19:17</a> <em>Slavery involves faithfulness to the Master's purpose</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:7-Luke17:10\">LUK 17:7–17:10</a> <em>Slavery involves diligence for the Master's good.</em></p>\n<h2>Creation is itself in slavery until Jesus Christ returns</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:22\">ROM 8:19–8:22</a></strong></p>",
